                            <comment id="86661" author="emoly.liu" created="Mon, 16 Jun 2014 06:51:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch landed to 2.6.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="72213" author="emoly.liu" created="Mon, 25 Nov 2013 07:06:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch tracking at: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/8387&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/8387&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="71125" author="rread" created="Fri, 8 Nov 2013 15:40:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I would prefer to see target initialization divided into two steps: low level formatting, and the registration with a specific Lustre filesystem.  The initial step would initialize ldiskfs, and the second step would assign the index, NIDs, mgsnode, etc, and then register it with the MGS.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
